tossup_question: -   –  Identify all of the following three types of collisions that conserve kinetic energy: 1) Elastic collision; 2) Partial inelastic collision; 3) Completely inelastic collision.
bonus_question: -   –  A 2.0 meter long, 100 kilogram horizontal uniform steel beam is supported 0.6 meters from the right end. To the nearest whole newton-meter, what is the gravitational torque about the support?
